oc:kn_4be00903 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring StreamableHTTPServerTransport" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use stateless transport (sessionIdGenerator: undefined) for most API-wrapping servers. Only use session-keyed transport maps if tools need to share state across calls in a session." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Stateless mode is simplest and sufficient for most API-wrapping use cases; stateful sessions add complexity and should only be used when truly needed" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_57952304 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any MCP server" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Set the `instructions` field on McpServer with tool-use hints that don't fit in individual tool descriptions, such as call-order preferences." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The instructions field lands directly in Claude's system prompt — it's the highest-leverage one-liner in the spec for correcting tool misuse" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_60299ac2 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When telling users how to connect to a deployed remote MCP server" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For Claude Desktop and Claude.ai, remote servers must be configured via Settings → Connectors → Add custom connector, NOT via claude_desktop_config.json — remote servers configured there are ignored." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Claude Desktop's config file only supports local stdio servers; remote HTTP servers must use the Connectors UI" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a758fa4a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SecurityImplication ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deploying a remote HTTP MCP server" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always validate the Origin header on /mcp endpoint — this is a spec MUST for DNS rebinding prevention." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without Origin validation, attackers can perform DNS rebinding attacks to interact with the MCP server from malicious web pages" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_b70c3f4f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before deploying any remote MCP server to production" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before deployment, verify: POST /mcp responds to initialize, tools/list returns complete schemas, errors return structured MCP errors (not HTTP 500 HTML), Origin header is validated, MCP-Protocol-Version is honored, CORS headers are set for browser clients, secrets come from env vars, and a separate health check endpoint exists." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These checks prevent common deployment failures including DNS rebinding attacks, version incompatibility, and unstructured error responses" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_c2843757 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing a hybrid tool surface for a large API" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Promote the 3–5 most-used actions to dedicated tools when using search + execute pattern. Keep the long tail behind search/execute." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Dedicated tools for top actions give Claude instant access to the most common operations without a discovery round-trip" .

oc:kn_ed23b3f1 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When wrapping large APIs with dozens to hundreds of endpoints" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not register 50+ individual tools when wrapping a large API surface. Use the search + execute pattern (two tools) instead." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Every tool schema costs tokens in Claude's context window each turn; flooding with 50+ tools degrades model performance" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

